$interpreted: Dylan: ...I'll get to the bottom of this and report it to King Theodore. Before the truth comes to light, we must swear to utmost secrecy.
Crushfang: Understood. We hope the Princess is found safe and sound.
Dylan: Sione, let's go.
Sione: Sir.
Dagger: How come only Dylan was sent to handle the situation? This is the time to send all Bear warriors in search of the princess!
Crushfang: This issue is the Kingdom of the Sun's. We cannot intervene.
Dagger: CANNOT INTERVENE? Someone disappeared on the Bear's territory! Isn't that scandalous enough? WHY aren't we doing something?!
Crushfang: Be calm. The Princess is almost twenty years old. Think the timing is a coincidence?
Dagger: Are you saying that...?!
Crushfang: All in all, the Bears cannot be too involved. Dylan promised to vouch for us,
Crushfang: and we shall wait patiently for news!
Dagger: Hmph! If that Dylan's words had weight to them, the Kingdom would never have kicked him out of the castle!
Dagger: I'm to blame for the princess' kidnapping. If you won't help, I'll find her on my own!
Crushfang: Can't you learn to keep your heart in check?!
Dagger: If your idea of calm is shrugging this off, I don't want to be what you expect of me!
Crushfang: If you insist on disobeying orders, you must challenge me, now!
Dagger: So, if you still want to fight, I won't go easy on you!
Crushfang: ...When have you become so...
Dagger: I won't always cower in his shadow, hiding like a defenseless cub!
Crushfang: I knew this day between us would finally come. Never did I expect it to be because you cared for a human...
Dagger: Claw your heart out. Anyway, I'm off to find the princess. Before I return to the Bears,
Dagger: my actions are not to be traced back to the tribe!
Old Priest: Hmm, this one has always been so impulsive.
Crushfang: Being impulsive at times is not always a bad thing.
Old Priest: What?
Crushfang: Didn't I say one day he'll change?
Crushfang: I think it just happened.
